{"id":"mai-zchu","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"P0: Support body updates via edit events","tags":["p0","core","event-sourced","ramboard"],"body":"## P0: Support body updates via edit events\n\n### Problem\n\nMaitake bodies are immutable after creation. The creation note's body never changes. This blocks ramboard's TipTap body editor — edits silently fail because there's no way to update a ticket's body through the CLI or engine.\n\n### Context (from ramboard rewiring session)\n\nRamboard was rewired to use `mai` as its backend instead of `.tickets/` files. Everything works except body editing. The hooman identified this as P0 because ticket bodies are the primary content — you can't have a ticket system where you can't edit the description.\n\nCurrent state in ramboard:\n- TipTap editor renders the body\n- Save calls `PATCH /api/projects/:id/tickets/:tid` with `{ body: '...' }`\n- Server has no way to pass this to maitake\n- The `ticket-writer.ts` logs a warning and does nothing\n\n### Proposed Design\n\nStay event-sourced. Add a new event kind `edit` that replaces the body:\n\n```\nkind event\nedge updates note:tre-5c4a\nfield body\n\nNew body content goes here.\nFull markdown. Replaces previous body on fold.\n```\n\nFold rule: `field body` → last-writer-wins by timestamp (same as other scalar fields).\n\n### Engine changes\n\n1. `AppendOptions` already has `Field` and `Body` — the fold logic in `applyFieldChange` needs a `case \"body\":` that sets `state.Body = ev.Body` (use the event's body, not `Value`)\n2. No new types needed\n\n### CLI changes\n\n```bash\nmai edit \u003cid\u003e -d \"new body content\"\nmai edit \u003cid\u003e  # opens $EDITOR with current body, saves diff as edit event\n```\n\n### What this unblocks\n\n- Ramboard body editing (TipTap save → `mai edit \u003cid\u003e -d \"...\"`)\n- Checkbox toggling (body mutation is just an edit event)\n- Any agent workflow that needs to update ticket descriptions\n- Priority updates (`field priority` — same pattern, also missing)\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `mai edit \u003cid\u003e -d \"new body\"` creates an edit event\n- [ ] `mai --json show \u003cid\u003e` returns the updated body after fold\n- [ ] `mai edit \u003cid\u003e` (no -d) opens $EDITOR\n- [ ] Multiple edits fold correctly (last-writer-wins)\n- [ ] Existing tests pass\n- [ ] Body edits appear in event history\n\n### Rejection Criteria\n\n- Mutating the creation note blob directly (breaks event-sourced model)\n- Storing body diffs instead of full replacement (complexity not worth it for v1)","timestamp":"2026-03-28T21:27:33Z","branch":"main"}
